production.line

Class Employee

  • java.lang.Object
    • production.line.Employee

  • public class Employee
extends java.lang.Object
    The program is required to create an audit trail of the production line so that it records which employee recorded production. To accomplish this you will need to create a class and tab named Employee that will allow the user to input their full name and then create a user id of their first name, a period, and then their surname, an email address of their first initial and last name.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Employee

        public Employee(java.lang.String fullName,
                java.lang.String password)
        The constructor Employee will accept a String for fullName (first name and surname) and String for password. It will append the fullName into a StringBuilder object. Using name, it will check the supplied name to set the username and email variable either through setUsername and setEmail or through default Strings in the checkName method. It will examine if the supplied password is valid, adhering to the password requirements of a lowercase, uppercase, and special character.
        Parameters:
        fullName - a String for the user's first and last name.
        password - a String for the user's provided password.
